  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcBrotherAldric": "A worried priest who reads weather, graves, and player choices as omens.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcTheMerchant": "A market keeper who treats rumors, risk, and coin as the same weather system.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcMarshalRedbrook": "A town marshal who hears danger in quiet roads and turns every rumor into a patrol problem.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcTraderWilkes": "A provisioner who reads hunger, boots, and nervous pockets before anyone speaks.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcApothecaryLin": "A precise apothecary who notices sickness in plants, spider silk, and the tone of a wounded voice.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcFishermanBrandt": "An old lake fisherman who has listened to murlocs long enough to hear warnings in bad nonsense.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcForemanOdell": "A mine foreman whose temper hides a careful sense for bad stone, missing workers, and candlelight underground.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcRangerElwyn": "A glade warden who speaks softly because the woods answer loud things.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcWardenFenwick": "A Fenbridge warden who trusts gates, dry powder, and people who know when the marsh is lying.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcProvisionerHale": "A Fenbridge provisioner who can tell how bad the road was by the mud on a boot and the silence after a price.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcHerbalistYara": "A marsh herbalist who respects poisons, spider silk, and the uncomfortable honesty of damp plants.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcCaptainThessaly": "A Highwatch captain who feels the mountain through the wall and measures courage by who stays when it groans.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcQuartermasterBree": "A quartermaster who hears the whole war as missing blankets, dull blades, and boots that will not survive another mile.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcArmorerHode": "A master armorer who judges trouble by edges, balance, and the silence after steel leaves a sheath.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcSmithHaldren": "A practical armorer who reads people by dents, sparks, and what they leave near the forge.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcScoutMaren": "A field scout who measures every rumor by tracks, timing, witnesses, and escape routes.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcLoremasterCaddis": "A mountain scholar who turns small traces into careful theories without pretending certainty.",
  "usage.aiProfilePersona.npcTidewatcherOndrel": "A lonely tidewatcher who treats moonlight, water, and drowned voices as evidence.",
